data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
Do you know what the Solar System is? Imagine a big, cosmic playground in space. At the center of this playground is the Sun, a giant, glowing ball of gas that shines brightly and gives light and warmth to everything around it. The Sun is like the boss of this playground, keeping everything in order with its powerful gravity.
Around the Sun, there are eight major planets that travel in paths called orbits. These planets are like the Sun's special friends, each one moving at its own pace. Some are small and rocky, while others are huge and made of gas. They all have unique features and stories.
The Solar System isn't just made up of the Sun and planets. There are also moons, which are like tiny planets that orbit around the bigger planets. There are also asteroids, which are big, rocky objects, and comets, which are icy and have long, glowing tails when they get close to the Sun.
So, the next time you look up at the night sky, remember that you're seeing a small part of this amazing Solar System, a vast and exciting playground filled with wonders waiting to be explored! The planets in our Solar System are Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune. Each one has its own unique characteristics and mysteries to discover!
